translation:
And “as for”
the believing men and the believing women, they are guardians of each other;
they enjoin good and forbid evil and keep up prayer and pay the poor – rate,
and obey Allah and his apostle; “as for” these, Allah will show mercy to them;
surely Allah is mighty, wise.

They shall
have covering of fire above them and covering beneath them; with that Allah
makes his servants to fear; so be careful of “your duty to” me, o my servants;

Surely those
who do not hope in our meeting and are pleased with this world’s life and are
content with it, and those who are heedless of our communication;

And “as for”
those who disbelieve, their deed are like the mirage in a desert, which the
thirsty man deems to be water; until when he comes to it he finds it to be
naught, and there he finds Allah, so he pays back to him his reckoning in full;
and Allah is quick in reckoning;

Have you not
seen those who have changed Allah’s favour for ungratefulness and made their
people to alight into the abode of perdition;

And if you
obey most of those in the earth, they will lead you astray from Allah is way;
they follow but conjecture and they only lie.

And they say:
why is not a sign sent to him from his lord? Say: the unseen is only for Allah;
there fore wait ____ surely I too, with you am of those who wait.

And “as for”
those who strive hard for us; we will most certainly guide them in our ways;
and Allah is most surely with the doers of good.

And he who sends down water from the
cloud according to a measure, then we raise to life there by a dead country;
even thus shall you be brought forth;

Most certainly we will question those
to whim “the apostles” were sent, and most certainly we will also question the
apostles;

And on the day when we will gather
from every nation a party from among those who rejected our communications,
then they shall be formed into groups.

And “as for” those who believe and do good, we
will certainly give them abode in the high places in gardens beneath which
rivers flow, abiding there in; how good the reward of the workers;

And he it is who accepts repentance from his
servants and pardons the evil deeds and pardons the evil deeds and he know what
you do;

So know that there is no God but Allah, and ask
protection for your fault and for the believing men and the believing women;
and Allah knows the place of your returning and the placed of your abiding.

I am commanded only that I should serve the lord
of this city, who has made it sacred, and his are all things; and I am
commanded that I should be of those who submit;

But if they do not answer you, then know that;
it revealed by Allah’s knowledge and that there is no god but he will you then
submit?

Say: if I err, I err only against my own soul,
and if I follow a right direction, it is because of what my lord reveals to me;
surely he is hearing, nigh.

And had it not been that we had already
established you, you would certainly have been near to incline to them a
little;

Say: I am only a mortal like you; it is revealed
to me that your god is one god, therefore follow the right way to him and ask
his forgiveness; and woe to the polytheists;

O you who believe! Be not for word in the
presence of Allah and his apostle, and be careful of “your duty to” Allah;
surely Allah is hearing, knowing.

O you who believe! Do not enter houses other
than your own houses until you have asked permission and saluted their inmates;
this is better for you, that you may be mindful.

And the recompense of evil is punishment like
it, but whoever forgives and amends, he shall have his reward from Allah;
surely he does not love the unjust.

Do you then hope that they would believe in you;
and a party from among them indeed used to hear the word of Allah, then altered
it after they had understood it, and they know “this”.

And we gave Musa the book and made it guidance
to the children of Israel,
saying: do not take protector bedsides me;

O followers of the book! Why do you dispute
about Ibrahim, when the Tavrat and the Injeel were not revealed till after him;
do you not then understand?

That Allah may reward the truthful for their
truth, and punish the hypocrites if he please or turn to them “mercifully”;
surely Allah is forgiving merciful.

Muhammad is the apostle of Allah, and those with
him are firm of heart against the unbelievers compassionate among themselves;
you will see them bowing down, prostrating themselves, seeking grace from Allah
and pleasure, their marks are in their faces because of the effect of prostration;
that is their description in the Tavrat and their description in the Injeel;
like as seed ____ produce that puts forth its sprout, then strengthens it, so
it becomes stout and stands firmly on its stem, delighting the sowers that he
may enrage the unbelievers on account of them; Allah has promised those among
them who believe and do good, for give ness and a great reward.

And when Musa said to his people: o my people! Why
do you give me trouble? And you know indeed that I am Allah’s apostle to you;
but when they turned aside, Allah does not guide the transgressing people.

And the recompense of evil is punishment like
it, but whoever forgives and amends, he shall have his reward from Allah;
surely he does not love the unjust.

He will forgive you your faults and cause you to
enter into gardens, beneath which rivers flow, and goodly dwellings in gardens
of perpetuity, that is the mighty achievement;

And on that day we will leave a part
of them in conflict with another part, and the trumpet will be blown, so we
will gather them all together;

And “we made” the wind “subservient”
to Sulaiman, which made a month’s journery in the morning and a month’s journey
in the evening, and we made a fountain of molten copper to flow out for him;
and of the jinn there were those who worked before him by the command of his lord;
and whoever turned a side from our command from among them, we made him taste
of the punishment of burning.

So when they ride in the ships they
call upon Allah, being sincerely obedient to him, but when he brings them safe to
the land, lo! They associate others “with him”;

So when harm afflicts a man he calls upon us;
then, when we give him a favour from us, he says: I have been given it only be
means of knowledge. Nay, it is a trial, but most of them do not know.

And “we destroyed” Qaroun and firon and Haman;
and certainly Musa come to them with clear arguments, but they behaved
haughtily in the land; yet they could not out strip “us”.

The like of what befell the people of Nuh and Ad
and Samood and those after them, and Allah does not desire injustice for “his”
servants;

So when they ride in the ships they
call upon Allah, being sincerely obedient to him, but when he brings them safe
to the land, lo! They associate others “with him”;

The idolaters have no right to visit
the mosques of Allah while bearing witness to unbelief against themselves;
these it is whose doings are null, and in the fire shall they abide.

And they have no knowledge of it;
they do not follow anything but conjecture, and surely conjecture does not
avail against the truth at all.

He said: this is a she ____ camel;
she shall have her portion of water, and you have your portion of water on an
appointed time;

O prophet! Say to your wives: if you
desire this world’s life and its adornment, then come, I will give you a
provision and allow you to depart a goodly departing;

O prophet! Why do you forbid “your
self” that which Allah has made lawful for you; you seek to please your wives;
and Allah is forgiving, merciful?

And keep up prayer in the two parts of the day
and in the first hours of the night; surely good deeds take away evil deeds;
this is a reminder to the mindful.

So that we might try them with respect to it;
and who ever turns aside from the reminder of his lord, he will make him enter
into an afflicting chastisement.

Who created the seven heavens one
above another; you see no in congruity in the creation of the beneficent god;
then look again, can you see any disorder?

Those who, should we establish them in the land,
will keep up prayer and pay the poor ____ rate and enjoin good and forbid evil;
and Allah’s is the end of affairs.

O you who believe! Do not enter houses other than
your own houses until you have asked permission and saluted their in mates;
this is better for you, that you may be mindful.

And do not turn your face away from people in
contempt, nor go about in the land exulting over much; surely Allah does not
love any self ___ conceited boaster;

And if two parties of the believers quarrel,
make peace between them; but if one of them acts wrong fully to wards the
other, fight that which acts wrong fully until it returns to Allah’s command;
then if it returns, make peace between them with justice and act equitably;
surely Allah loves those who act equitably.

And do not turn your
face away from people in contempt, nor go about in the land exulting overmuch;
surely Allah does not love any self ____ conceited boaster;

And do not approach
the property of the orphan except in the best manner until he attains his
maturity; and give full measure and weight with justice ____ we do not impose
on any soul a duty except to the extent of its ability; and when you speak;
then be just though it be “against” a relative, and fulfil Allah’s covenant;
this he has enjoined you with that you may be mindful.

And do not turn your
face away from people in contempt or go about is the land exulting over much;
surely Allah does not love any self ____ conceited boaster;

O my son! Keep up
prayer and enjoin the good and forbid the evil, and bear patiently that which
befalls you; surely these acts require courage;

Therefore be patient;
surely the promise of Allah is true; and ask protection for your fault and sing
the praise of your lord in the evening and the morning.

And do not approach
the property of the orphan except in the best manner until he attains his
maturity; and give full measure and weight with justice ____ we do not impose
on any soul a duty except to the extent of its ability; and when you speak,
then be just though it be “against”” a relative and fulfil Allah’s covenant;
this he has enjoined you with that you may be mindful;

Say: surely my prayer
and my sacrifice and my life and my death are “all” for Allah, the lord of the
world;

Whoever then alters it
after he has heard it, the sin of it then is only upon those who alter it;
surely Allah is hearing, knowing.

And do not turn your
face away from people in contempt, nor go about in the land exulting over much;
surely Allah does not love any self ____ conceited boaster;

So that you may not
grieve for what has escaped you, nor be exultant at what he has given you; and
Allah does not love any arrogant boaster;

And do not turn your face away from
people in contempt, nor go about in the land exulting over much; surely Allah
does not love any ____ conceited boaster;

Except the weak from among the men
and the children who have not in their power the means nor can they find a way
“to escape”;

O you who believe! Do not devour your
property among yourselves falsely, except that it be trading by your mutual consent;
and do not kill your people; surely Allah is merciful to you.

O my people! This life of the world
is only a ”passing” enjoyment, and surely the here after is the abode to
settle;

No evil befalls on the earth or in
your own souls, but it is in a book before we bring it into existence; surely
that is easy to Allah;

These are they whom Allah guided,
there fore follow their guidance, say: I do not ask you for any reward for it;
it is nothing but a reminder to the nations.

And those who disbelieve say: this is
nothing but a lie which he has forged, and other people have helped him at it;
so indeed they have done injustice and ”uttered” a false hood.

It may be that Allah will bring about
friend ship between you and those whom you hold to be your enemies among them;
and Allah is powerful; and Allah is powerful; and Allah is forgiving, merciful.

Do not hold the
apostle’s calling ”you” among you to be like your calling one to the other;
Allah in deed knows those who steal away from among you, concealing themselves;
therefore let those beware who go against his order lest a trial afflict them
or there befall them a painful chastisement.

So when they ride in
the ships they call upon Allah, being sincerely obedient to him, but when he
brings them safe to the land, lo! They associate others ”with him”;

And ”we sent”
apostles we have mentioned to you before and apostles we have not mentioned to
you; and to Musa, Allah addressed his word, speaking ”to him”;

Certainly then we will
question those to whom ”the apostles” were sent and most certainly we will
also question the apostles;

And thus, we did not
send before you any warner in a town, but those who led easy lives in it said;
and surely we are followers of their footsteps.

He said: this is a she
____ camel; she shall have her portion of water, and you have your portion of
water on an appointed time;

So they have indeed
rejected the truth when it came to them; therefore the truth of what they
mocked at will shine upon them;

And how many a living
creature that does not carry its sustenance: Allah sustains it and your selves;
and he is the hearing, the knowing.

Our lord! Surely who
so ever thou makest enter the fire, him thou hast indeed brought to disgrace,
and there shall be no helpers for the unjust;

And they shall say: o
our lord! Surely we obeyed our leaders and our great men, so they led us as
tray from the path;
